feigned to give a false appearance of; to imitate so as to deceive
exempt free from an obligation, a duty, or a liability to which others are subject
bizarre strikingly unconventional and far-fetched in style or appearance; odd
bantering to speak to in a playful or teasing way
complacency a feeling of contentment or self-satisfaction, especially when coupled with an unawareness of danger, trouble, or controversy
intimation an indirect suggestion; a slight suggestion or vague understanding
desolate devoid of inhabitants; deserted
supercilious feeling or showing haughty disdain; proud
contiguous sharing an edge or boundary; touching
apathetic feeling or showing a lack of interest or concern; indifferent
languid lacking energy or vitality; weak
